: "(memes don't need titles)", "last_comment_created": 1776318014486, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 1, "score_up": 45, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZR0kEw0", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 74, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8561644, "raw_content": "", "author": "Oruin", "created": 1776304638495, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "HillarysBeaverMunch", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "nypost.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZR0kEw0.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://nypost.com/2026/04/15/us-news/carnival-cruise-passenger-wins-300k-lawsuit-after-being-served-14-tequila-shots-and-taking-massive-fall/", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Miami Jury Finds White Women Are Incapable of Controlling Themselves, and Place the Burden of Their Care Upon Society.", "last_comment_created": 1776341492963, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 13, "score_up": 74, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "\u201cShe woke up, not knowing exactly how she got there at the bottom of the staircase in the crew area,\u201d the California nurse\u2019s lawyer, Spencer Aronfeld, said of his client.", "large_image": "jJG8ed0SuGFkRrVB.png", "title": "Carnival cruise passenger wins $300K lawsuit after being overserved with 14 tequila shots before massive fall"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZR1rXG4", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 11, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8562240, "raw_content": "Why it is  Important to Fully Appreciate the Word of God\r\n\u201cEvery word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him. Add you not unto his words, lest he reprove you, and you be found a liar.\u201d (Proverbs 30:5-6) \r\n\nIt is important to have a clear understanding that every word of God is pure, emphasizing its truth and reliability. When this knowledge is applied, God  promises to serves as a shield to those who take refuge in Him, offering His all-powerful protection.\r\nThis passage not only provides us with confidence in His protection, but it also warns those who hold the Word of God with contempt. God warns against adding to God's words, highlighting the importance of integrity in communication. \r\n\nGod gives us similar warning in Revelation 22:18-19, \u201cFor I testify unto every man that hears the words of the prophecy of this book, If any man shall add unto these things, God shall add unto him the plagues that are written in this book: 19 And if any man shall take away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God shall take away his part out of the book of life, and out of the holy city, and from the things which are written in this book.\u201d\r\n\nIt stresses the consequences of misrepresenting divine truth, which can lead to judgment. At the same time, this passage of scripture encourages believers to trust in God's wisdom and guidance with a steadfast hope.\r\n\nOne of the judgments to those who are indifferent toward the Word of God is given to us in Romans 1:18-25, \u201cFor the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and unrighteousness of men, who hold the truth in unrighteousness; 19 Because that which may be known of God is manifest in them; for God has showed it unto them. 20 For the invisible things of him from the creation of the world are clearly seen, being understood by the things that are made, even his eternal power and Godhead; so that they are without excuse: 21 Because that, when they knew God, they glorified him not as God, neither were thankful; but became vain in their imaginations, and their foolish heart was darkened. 22 Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools, 23  And changed the glory of the uncorruptible God into an image made like to corruptible man, and to birds, and fourfooted beasts, and creeping things. 24 Wherefore God also gave them up to uncleanness through the lusts of their own hearts, to dishonor their own bodies between themselves: 25 Who changed the truth of God into a lie, and worshipped and served the creature more than the Creator, who is blessed for ever. Amen. 26 For this cause God gave them up unto vile affections: for even their women did change the natural use into that which is against nature.\u201d Two times, God tells us that HE GIVES THEM UP -- those who reject God\u2019s Word.\r\n", "author": "Come-mistertallyman", "created": 1776341901058, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Why it is Important to Fully Appreciate the Word of God", "last_comment_created": 1776341901057, "content": "<p>Why it is  Important to Fully Appreciate the Word of God\n\u201cEvery word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him. Add you not unto his words, lest he reprove you, and you be found a liar.\u201d (Proverbs 30:5-6)</p>\n<p>It is important to have a clear understanding that every word of God is pure, emphasizing its truth and reliability. When this knowledge is applied, God  promises to serves as a shield to those who take refuge in Him, offering His all-powerful protection.\nThis passage not only provides us with confidence in His protection, but it also warns those who hold the Word of God with contempt. God warns against adding to God's words, highlighting the importance of integrity in communication.</p>\n<p>God gives us similar warning in Revelation 22:18-19, \u201cFor I testify unto every man that hears the words of the prophecy of this book, If any man shall add unto these things, God shall add unto him the plagues that are written in this book: 19 And if any man shall take away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God shall take away his part out of the book of life, and out of the holy city, and from the things which are written in this book.\u201d</p>\n<p>It stresses the consequences of misrepresenting divine truth, which can lead to judgment. At the same time, this passage of scripture encourages believers to trust in God's wisdom and guidance with a steadfast hope.</p>\n<p>One of the judgments to those who are indifferent toward the Word of God is given to us in Romans 1:18-25, \u201cFor the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and unrighteousness of men, who hold the truth in unrighteousness; 19 Because that which may be known of God is manifest in them; for God has showed it unto them. 20 For the invisible things of him from the creation of the world are clearly seen, being understood by the things that are made, even his eternal power and Godhead; so that they are without excuse: 21 Because that, when they knew God, they glorified him not as God, neither were thankful; but became vain in their imaginations, and their foolish heart was darkened. 22 Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools, 23  And changed the glory of the uncorruptible God into an image made like to corruptible man, and to birds, and fourfooted beasts, and creeping things. 24 Wherefore God also gave them up to uncleanness through the lusts of their own hearts, to dishonor their own bodies between themselves: 25 Who changed the truth of God into a lie, and worshipped and served the creature more than the Creator, who is blessed for ever. Amen. 26 For this cause God gave them up unto vile affections: for even their women did change the natural use into that which is against nature.\u201d Two times, God tells us that HE GIVES THEM UP -- those who reject God\u2019s Word.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 11, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZQzb14G", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 775, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8560314, "raw_content": "", "author": "DingleBalls", "created": 1776258444825, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "BigPlains", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "nj1015.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZQzb14G.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://nj1015.com/spadea-to-pope-leo-cardinal-tobin/", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Spadea to Pope Leo & Cardinal Tobin: Stay in your lane", "last_comment_created": 1776302633368, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_im